    <abstract id="aspace_63c8a7bbf73aea080a56253eb7c8f923">Ronald Vance is an artist and writer active in the United States and Europe during the later half of the 20th century. This collection consists of correspondence, as well as published and unpublished writings by Vance from the late 1960s through the mid 1980s. Works of fiction present in the collection were published in literary journals including <title render="italic">Sun and Moon</title>, <title render="italic">Not Guilty Magazine</title>, and <title render="italic">Interstate Magazine</title>. The collection also includes unpublished writings, including notes and drafts related to Vance's <title render="italic">I Went to Italy and Ate Chocolate</title>.</abstract>
    <langmaterial id="aspace_afd276b6469a7a78d2cd0e456ac4bc60">Materials are in English.</langmaterial>
  </did>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_48ebb40677a34c3f5b10778cbb1b1a23">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>This collection consists of correspondence, as well as published and unpublished writings by Ronald Vance from the late 1960s through the mid 1980s. Works of fiction present in the collection were published in literary journals including <title render="italic">Sun and Moon</title>, <title render="italic">Not Guilty Magazine</title>, and <title render="italic">Interstate Magazine</title>. The collection also includes unpublished writings, including notes and drafts related to Vance's <title render="italic">I Went to Italy and Ate Chocolate</title>.</p>  </scopecontent>
