  <arrangement id="aspace_b7bc096a1a825c3c47c629cbc7e7e3dc">
    <head>Arrangement</head>
<p>This collection has not been arranged by an archivist. The materials are arranged in the order in which they were received from the donor.</p>  </arrangement>
  <bioghist id="aspace_de7bec5ab1fcc2afeac4a075701d14f5">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Ronald Vance is an artist and writer active during the 1960s through the 1980s. He was born in Connecticut and graduated from Yale University before lecturing on the history of art at Leicester College of Art and then moving to Italy. As of May 2016, he was living in Long Island and was retired.</p>  </bioghist>
  <userestrict id="aspace_9a48833c90e29c5e24c4cc13e2c0ea6d">
    <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
<p>Any rights (including copyright and related rights to publicity and privacy) held by Ronald Vance, were transferred to New York University in 2016 by Ronald Vance. Permission to publish or reproduce materials in this collection must be secured from the Fales Library and Special Collections. Please contact fales.library@nyu.edu, 212-998-2596.</p>  </userestrict>
  <acqinfo id="aspace_6170a1a87ba1c9e9e3361788b04575ec">
    <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
<p>Donated by Ronald Vance in May 2016. The accession number associated with this gift is 2016.023.</p>  </acqinfo>
